title: Grateful Dead Live at San Francisco Civic Auditorium on 1987-01-28
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Taped & transferred by Andrew F. 02/2012 - matrix mixing by Kevin Tobin
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Get Back, Peggy-O, Walkin' Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy, My Brother Esau, Bird Song, Jack Straw

Set 2

When Push Comes To Shove, Samson & Delilah-> Black Muddy River-> He's Gone-> Spoonful-> Drums*-> Eyes Of The World-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

*With extra drummer

reviews.review_text:
WOW!!! This sounds fantastic in 5.1! 
Beautifully well-done matrix!
Thank you!
- The sound is indeed excellent. Unfortunately the show is a bit of a clunker. No one remembers the words to anything and the playing is generally substandard.
